1 AN ACT concerning health and healthcare; relating to the department of
2 health and environment; requiring the department to submit an annual
3 report to the legislature concerning the newborn screening program;
4 specifying the contents of the report.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. On or before April 1, 2026, and annually thereafter, the
8 department of health and environment shall submit a report to the senate
9 standing committee on public health and welfare and the house of
10 representatives standing committee on health and human services or their
11 successor committees on the Kansas newborn screening program. The
12 report shall be developed by the department of health and environment
13 newborn screening staff, the Kansas newborn screening advisory council
14 and disability and rare disease advocacy organizations. Such report shall
15 include:
16 (a) The disorders currently screened under the Kansas newborn
17 screening program;
18 (b) new disorders under consideration or recommended for inclusion,
19 including the amount of funding needed to implement such screenings;
20 (c) disorders considered but not recommended for inclusion during
21 the prior 12 months, including the explanations for their exclusion;
22 (d) disorders that the department determined do not require
23 reevaluation within the prior 12 months, including the reasons for such
24 determinations; and
25 (e) any delays in meeting the specified timelines for evaluating,
26 including or reevaluating disorders, including the reasons for the delays.
27 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
28 publication in the statute book.

